The paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a problem in computer vision and multimedia analysis. The proposed method uses deep learning techniques to model a novel set to set distance metric, which is a common approach in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves large margin learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely category. The paper also involves multimedia analysis and content-based media retrieval, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the third likely category. The paper also involves information retrieval and matching, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper involves security and privacy, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the fifth likely category.
